teal.field

Class CompositeField

  • java.lang.Object
    • teal.field.Field
      • teal.field.CompositeField
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Vector3dField
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BField, EField, GField, PField

    public abstract class CompositeField
extends Field
    CompositeField represents the composite field generated by a series of objects. It is used by the simulation to compute the total field at any given position due to the appropriate field-generating elements in the scene.

      • get

        public abstract javax.vecmath.Vector3d get(javax.vecmath.Vector3d x,
                                           TElement excludeObj)
        The abstract method "get()" is the generalized function for returning the value of the CompositeField at the given position. It should be implemented in derived classes according to the specific field type that the CompositeField represents (ie. EField, BField, etc.). The supplied TElement should be excluded from contributing to the total field as a way to determine the field acting on that object (an object does not feel it's own field).
        Parameters:
        x - Position at which to calculate the total field.
        excludeObj - Object to exclude from the calculation.
        Returns:
        Total field, minus the field generated by excludeObj, at x.
